<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>What I find amazingly hard to believe is that you believe Bush is scheming to take over the world, while Saddaam and Kim Jong Il are merely trying to better their country and live happy little dictatorial lives in peace.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
All I said was the new tension over North Korea was manufactured by the Bush administration. He's not doing it to take over the world, he's trying to destabilise the world to benefit his financial backers and stimulate US industry. Do you realise how much of your money Bush is handing over to the arms industry through new military spending, and to the drug industry through bioterrorism &quot;precautions&quot;?.<br>
<br>
Saddam and Kim Jong Il are evil dictators who are trying to better themselves, not their countries. But they have a record of responding to negotiation on the basis of &quot;if you behave, we will help you&quot;. Under Bush, that is not offered -- negotiation now consists of &quot;if you misbehave, we will hit you&quot;. <p>--<br>
