<br>
England made sure germany was not producing arms....<br>
<br>
The U.S. Has inspectors in both countries, Iraq and Nkorea.<br>
<br>
Germany began to produce arms/weapons....England Afraid of another conflict ( Partially because they were still recovering from WW1) Turned a blind eye to the build up.<br>
<br>
You would like the U.S. to respect Iraq/Nkoreas Sovereignty. Which means to avert war we will apease them by turning a blind eye to their weapons build up. Now if they do nothing but defend themselves with the weapons they produce then that is great, However that is not what happened 60 years ago.....<br>
 <br>
Germany/Japan quickly began striking other countries after their weapons build up. And the war quickly escelated into world war 2, Involving many nations and countless millions died.<br>
<br>
What IF North Korea is thinking the same thing, The death tole of WW2 would be magnified 100 times if nukes were used. <br>
<br>
England and france could have saved the lives of countless millions by taking action against germany, The U.S. could have saved millions by taking action against germany. None of us did anything, And 50 million (or so) people died because of that.<br>
<br>
60 Years from now, Will our children be talking much like we are now, And asking why the U.S. did nothing when Nkorea was arming up, Why we ignored Iraq's Agressive actions. Could we have stopped 500 million peoples deaths?<br>
<br>
Todays situation has a startling simmilarity to the start of WW2, However if it does go down the same road the next war might be the end of us all. In WW2 people with power chose to do nothing, Should we also do nothing. Would we be making the same mistake we made 60 years ago? This time would more people die because of our blunder?<br>
