<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.commondreams.org/views02/0802-01.htm" target="top">The Saddam in Rumsfelds Closet </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
Now, aside from the moral issus, this shows us something important. If Saddams WMD were not a threat to us at that time, why does Bush expect us to believe they are now? If you say his invasion of kuwait is what makes him a threat to us, consider the fact that no WMD were used during that invasion.<br>
<br>
Now don't get me wrong - this is not a &quot;we should have never allied with Iraq&quot; argument. Iran was the problem at that point and my enemies enemy is my friend. But, we had no moral qualms with him gassing Curds back then and we didn't see his WMD as a threat. Why? Because they weren't.<br>
<br>
Now I will conceed that maybe Saddam has WMD. But, he has no delivery system other than scuds, which lack the range to threaten us. He didn't use them when invading Kuwait. Surely ig he's as mad as Bush likes to make him out, he would have frely used WMD in his invasion.<br>
<br>
I certainly won't argue that he doesn't want WMD... especially nukes. But wanting them and having the means to build them are two different things. Also, our arguments are hypocritical when you consider what he was doing when he was our friend and the fact that we helped him do it and the fact that these WMD were not a threat to us then but somehow they are now.<br>
